                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.192/3: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Panama</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">South</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-01-30T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 30, 1924—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>11. Your 11, January 29, 3 p.m. You may inform Panaman Government that this
                    Government is willing to appoint a Commission to negotiate treaty with Panaman
                    Commission and is willing to commence negotiations in Washington at convenience
                    of Panaman Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
